        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow"><span class="num">No. 03</span><span class="rule-mini"></span>Founding principles</div>
          <h2 style="margin-top: 14px;">The four rules they <em>wrote down.</em></h2>
        </div>
        <p>
          The cooperative still runs on the structure <span class="placeholder placeholder-inline">[Brodsky and Greenberg]</span> drafted in the first year. Four short rules &mdash; codified in the founding documents, ratified by the Member Council, and unchanged in substance since.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <div class="num">01</div>
          <h4>Owned by the operators it serves.</h4>
          <p>Every member company holds a stake in the cooperative. No outside investors. No private equity backing. No founders who exited and kept the equity.</p>
          <span class="meta">Rule &middot; 01 &middot; Ownership</span>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="num">02</div>
          <h4>Membership grows by introduction.</h4>
          <p>A current member nominates a peer. A peer takes the call. If the fit is real, the room expands. No prospecting. No cold outreach. No volume targets.</p>
          <span class="meta">Rule &middot; 02 &middot; Growth</span>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="num">03</div>
          <h4>One company, one vote.</h4>
          <p>Every cooperative-wide decision &mdash; admissions, vendor lineup, the annual program, governance changes &mdash; carries equal weight per member company. Portfolio size doesn&rsquo;t buy more votes.</p>
          <span class="meta">Rule &middot; 03 &middot; Governance</span>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <div class="num">04</div>
          <h4>Vendors earn the slot, every year.</h4>
          <p>No vendor pays the cooperative to be featured. Partners earn their place by member-rated performance and defend it annually. Members can vote a vendor out at any review cycle.</p>
          <span class="meta">Rule &middot; 04 &middot; Independence</span>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
